rect.title: Distance travelled is the total length of the actual path travelled by an object irrespective of the direction of motion
Displacement is defined as the distance moved in a specific direction
Speed is defined as the distance travelled per unit time OR the rate of change of distance travelled
Velocity is defined as the displacement per unit time OR the rate of change of displacement
Acceleration is defined as the rate of change of velocity
The gradient of the v-t graph at any instant is the instantaneous acceleration of the body. The area under the v-t graph is the change in displacement of the body within the time interval
The gradient of the displacement-time graph at any instant is the instantaneous velocity of the body
Area under the a-t graph is the change in velocity of the body.

1.Sketch diagram 2.Set sign convention + direction as the direction of the initial velocity u 3.Choose start and end point. 4.Identify known and unknown quantities. 5.Identify suitable equation 6.Substitute and solve 7.is answer sensible?
